# CODEOWNERS — path-based review routing for Vaipakam.
#
# Why this file exists:
# --------------------
# 1. It tells GitHub who to auto-request review from when a PR touches a path.
# 2. It documents OWNERSHIP for auditors — "who is responsible for THIS code?".
#    The answer happens to be the same person today (solo dev), but the
#    STRUCTURE makes the load-bearing subsystems visible and creates the
#    scaffolding for additional reviewers / contributors to be slotted in
#    later without re-architecting governance.
#
# Conventions:
# - Path globs follow .gitignore-style matching.
# - The LAST matching pattern wins. Order matters — go from broadest to
#   narrowest (catch-all first, specific subsystems below).
# - Branch-protection on `main` requires the CODEOWNERS reviewer to approve
#   any PR touching their paths (per `Protect main` ruleset; see
#   `docs/internal/ProjectProcedures.md` §7).

